posts.body:
>>be0d0274-29b8-46f9-ab04-b0a1ae22746a
I can't post anything there - suspect shenanigans. So I guess people are still hunting through these other alternatives for the new home.
Well, it's straight up Putin propaganda honestly - but hey, still more accurate than (((Western))) media.
Screenshot of the news breaking BEFORE it was reported by the media - posted to 4/pol/

>>98aec590-9a55-4b34-8ed8-34257c5e1e60
I get a lot of console errors (and the odd memory leak that's required a hard reboot)  that I assume are from false seeds. I'd rather see Millchan or 0chan take off honestly - and I'm not going back to 8chan. It's time to leave the clearnet behind entirely.

Interesting - TV news in Straya get's cut off mid-sentence when discussing the case. It's mind boggling just how little effort (((they))) are putting in to covering this up - even most rank normies aren't buying it.

>>9f71ae96-4dac-43cc-9cd7-3b151915e9c3
> DIfferent hash
Reminder - write a script YOURSELF (it's not too hard, learn python or something else brainlet-level simple) that'll strip metadata, pad the file to alter the hash & change the filename of anything you submit to prevent tracking, especially if you're posting across sites or using an identity that could dox you.

IPFS is a good idea to use for a DHT, and I can see a case for using Ethereum for a few things like immutable content that's available regardless of seeding & smart contracts could be handy as anons could post tokens to each other, but fuck Ripple. Centralized POS jewcoin.
